description.narrative: Media Alliance for children's rights is established, and together with CSOs (including CSOs from Serbian-majority municipalities), is influencing public policy and demand for realization of child rights, and holding Institutions in Kosovo accountable for realization of children's rights, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Policy Advocacy â€“ Urban, Civil Society, Parliament, Environment, Social Exclusion â€“ Data And Evidence. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, institutions in Kosovo at central and municipal levels are accountable and responsive to monitoring children's rights, promoting social inclusion, and advancing a social protection system (grants and services) that is also responsive to the needs of the most marginalized children (including vulnerable returnee children belonging to all ethnic communities)

description.narrative: Risk communication information materials developed by UNICEF have been a notable component of the overall COVID-19 Kosovo response lead by the Ministry of Health. To emphasize the emerging need to further invest on inclusion of children with disabilities, UNICEF Kosovo led a nationwide campaign which resulted in mobilization of public and private institutions for advancing the agenda of inclusion in Kosovo. Partnering with media, private sector, influencers and public institutions placed UNICEF’s Kosovo three key programme priorities higher on the agenda of public discussion and more than 7 million people were reached through social media. | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/01/2021
